$675
Translation of Patent Sentences with a Large Vocabulary of Technical Terms Using Neural Machine Translation proposes an NMT method for patent sentence translation with many infrequent technical terms. It trains on bilingual data where technical terms are replaced by technical term tokens, uses NMT to translate source sentences with those tokens, replaces tokens with SMT-based technical term translations, and reranks 1,000-best SMT outputs using the average of SMT score and NMT rescoring. On Japanese-Chinese patent sentences, it improves by up to 3.1 BLEU and 2.3 RIBES over traditional SMT, and by about 0.6 BLEU and 0.8 RIBES over equivalent NMT without the technique.
